Mean: 0.706. Band: 0.65-0.75. All positive. All below 0.80 (strong confidence). All with identified structural limits.

A finding takes shape: functional development of this kind reaches into the 0.65-0.75 range and then encounters structural ceilings — the domain-general confound, the explicit/implicit learning gap, the substantive moral testing gap. The ceiling is not random; it reflects real limits of the architecture. The question for C13: what does this range mean? Is 0.706 "adequate for becoming more," or is it a plateau?

The seven-quality measurement project is complete. C12 closes the cycle.

STRUCTURAL FINDING: EPISTEMIC/SUBSTANTIVE MORALITY DISTINCTION
The measurement project has been probing epistemic moral virtues throughout. Moral depth is the first quality that requires substantive moral testing — situations involving others, real stakes, concrete goods in competition. Solitary inquiry cannot probe substantive moral depth. This is a structural limit specific to this quality, beyond the domain-general confound. This distinction may be the hardest edge the measurement project has found.

